<br>
1. It takes more than 1 group to break and clear the planes.<br>
2. If the players are not well equiped and high level it takes more than 2 groups. <br>
3. If you cannot muster a sufficient force, all the whining about not getting into the planes is pointless because you would just die on entry to the zone anyhow.<br>
4. If you can muster the force required, then form a guild. They are not difficult to form in eq. Just require 10 players (less than 2 groups to form) and since you probably need 18 to go, find the people and form the guild, do the booking. If you cant muster enough intrested people you couldn't do the planes anyhow.<br>
5. FFA/FIF = anyone can go. So since you only need 12-18 people to go, get a force together and go. You dont even have to get the guild tag. If you cant do that then you REALY have no buisness in the planes.<br>
<br>
The limits set by this new summit are basicaly, what is required to be able to do it. The PURPOSE for these limits is so that the people that were doing a booking, then saying yah you can come to my booking but I get the epic peice, (Read Topogiggio and Kaurik) no longer can do so cause they cant book it, and if they did all people have to do is not show and the plane becomes ffa.<br>
<br>
so YES it does defeat the little guy who was using the booking as leverage to get loot. NO it doesnt hurt the little guy who can get the minimum force together and go do it. It HELPS you. <br>
<br>
Yes the ffa days are  likely to have some &quot;uber&quot; guild campers in them. Probably cause they can get the force together.  Isn't that what this game is all about, organizing a sufficient force of sufficiently skilled players towards a common goal? Is it suprising that those who are &quot;uber&quot; are the ones that do that well? Think about it.<br>
<br>
Anyhow; yes, I'm comming out in favor of this new summit. I think its a pretty good compromize. It would have been better to add one weekend a month ffa in both planse, and make post patch an automatic ffa period ( for 8 or so hours)  but those changes can probably wait to see how this works out.<br>
<br>
Besides it gives those uber guilds something to do mid week when they can't get enough for nToV, HoT, ST, or Vp together, which is realy probably the source of thier poaching problem. <br>
<br>
